.. activecode:: 2D_tables_AC_1
  :author: bmiller
  :difficulty: 3
  :basecourse: thinkcpp
  :topic: Chapter6/two_dimensional_tables
  :from_source: T
  :language: cpp
  :caption: Two-dimensional tables

  Run the active code below, which uses a simple loop that prints the multiples
  of 2, all on one line.
  ~~~~
  #include <iostream>
  using namespace std;

  int main() {
      int i = 1;
      while (i <= 6) {
          cout << 2*i << "   ";
          i = i + 1;
      }
      cout << endl;
      return 0;
  }